Yeah man, it really never gets old. Id by crying with laughter at 12 watching Michael Rosen, the chuckle brothers, how it's made, Billy Mays, and whatever else was on the YTP menu. 

Also I actually bumped into Michael Rosen on the street once and I just didn't know what to say, all of the YTP profanities flashed before my eyes, he had been a real formative element of my humour but only through the bastardisation of his material so I just said "thankyou for your poetry" and left it at that.

